Eskom is again teetering on the edge of rolling blackouts with unplanned breakdowns at 12,535MW as of 7am yesterday, just 76MW short of the 13 302MW which saw Eskom move to stage 2 load shedding nine days ago. “There is no load shedding expected today as a result of a drop in demand during the holiday period and a return of some generating units into service. Eskom will continue to use emergency reserves to supplement capacity if necessary over this period,” the utility said. As the system continued to “be vulnerable and unpredictable”, the possibility of load shedding remained, Eskom...